1
00:00:07,721 --> 00:00:09,481
[If you don't turn yourself in,
your limbs will rot and you'll die]

2
00:00:37,938 --> 00:00:41,338
[All characters and events are fictional,
and any resemblance is coincidental]

3
00:00:41,338 --> 00:00:43,972
[Scenes with children and animals were filmed
safely under professional supervision]

4
00:00:43,972 --> 00:00:47,805
[Law and Order, Positive Change]
You're back. What about your paper?

5
00:00:47,805 --> 00:00:49,505
[With a dream, you can start again]
Thanks to you, it went well.

6
00:00:50,205 --> 00:00:52,838
Did you solve the riddle I gave you?

7
00:00:58,338 --> 00:01:00,438
[Murder: 12+2, Rape: 19, Attempted: 15]
12 plus 2.

8
00:01:00,438 --> 00:01:03,005
That makes 14 murders in total.

9
00:01:03,005 --> 00:01:06,005
Are you saying there are
five more unknown murders?

10
00:01:06,005 --> 00:01:09,672
I knew you'd figure it out, Professor.

11
00:01:11,305 --> 00:01:15,338
I'll admit to all acts related to
the nine cases already known.

12
00:01:15,338 --> 00:01:18,738
And I'll honestly confess the rest as well.

13
00:01:18,738 --> 00:01:20,605
But

14
00:01:20,605 --> 00:01:23,672
only if you tell me something, Professor.

15
00:01:23,672 --> 00:01:24,772
Tell you about what?

16
00:01:24,772 --> 00:01:26,472
About you, Professor.

17
00:01:26,472 --> 00:01:27,838
You said you lost everything.

18
00:01:27,838 --> 00:01:31,372
Tell me exactly what you lost.

19
00:01:31,372 --> 00:01:33,005
For each answer,

20
00:01:35,038 --> 00:01:37,772
one hidden murder.

21
00:01:37,772 --> 00:01:39,472
Fair enough, isn't it?

22
00:01:41,638 --> 00:01:44,905
[Murder: 12+2, Rape: 19, Attempted: 15]

23
00:01:55,205 --> 00:01:57,535
If you're not willing to talk,

24
00:01:57,535 --> 00:02:00,305
I'll take my secret to the grave.

25
00:02:03,105 --> 00:02:06,072
Alright, let's do that.

26
00:02:07,738 --> 00:02:10,372
Now, it's getting interesting.

27
00:02:11,605 --> 00:02:13,538
Start with your side of the story.

28
00:02:13,538 --> 00:02:16,205
What exactly did you lose?

29
00:02:19,872 --> 00:02:23,272
I lost my friend.

30
00:02:30,572 --> 00:02:32,672
You've done a great job.

31
00:02:32,672 --> 00:02:35,172
I knew you'd pull it off, Prosecutor Cha.

32
00:02:35,938 --> 00:02:38,038
[Episode 6]
It's all thanks to you, sir.

33
00:02:38,038 --> 00:02:42,305
Now that we've identified the suspect,
catching him will be easy.

34
00:02:42,305 --> 00:02:44,938
Now I can finally get some peace of mind.

35
00:03:01,105 --> 00:03:03,172
What are you staring at so intently?

36
00:03:08,972 --> 00:03:11,672
Do you see this date?

37
00:03:11,672 --> 00:03:14,205
[December 13, 1987]
That's the day Choi In Sook went missing.

38
00:03:14,205 --> 00:03:17,172
- What?
- When Choi In Sook was murdered,

39
00:03:17,838 --> 00:03:20,072
Ki Beom was with me.

40
00:03:20,072 --> 00:03:22,872
Then why is Park Ae Sook's purse
in the bookstore?

41
00:03:23,872 --> 00:03:25,672
If it was not Lee Ki Beom...

42
00:03:28,605 --> 00:03:29,929
Could it be

43
00:03:29,929 --> 00:03:31,672
Lee Ki Beom's brother?

44
00:03:37,005 --> 00:03:39,038
Hey, what do you mean?

45
00:03:39,038 --> 00:03:41,872
Are you saying
he might not be the real killer?

46
00:03:42,638 --> 00:03:44,918
When Choi In Sook was murdered,

47
00:03:44,918 --> 00:03:46,185
Ki Beom was with me.

48
00:03:46,185 --> 00:03:47,805
[Wedding Reception
December 13, 1987]

49
00:03:47,805 --> 00:03:49,938
Just give me more time.

50
00:03:49,938 --> 00:03:52,105
Look, I've got a press conference
in 10 minutes.

51
00:03:52,105 --> 00:03:54,138
I was about to announce
we've identified the suspect.

52
00:03:54,138 --> 00:03:57,705
Why rush a press conference
like this all of a sudden?

53
00:03:57,705 --> 00:04:01,205
You're the one who wanted to rush this case.

54
00:04:01,205 --> 00:04:02,672
When did I say that?

55
00:04:02,672 --> 00:04:04,538
Anyway, cover this up.

56
00:04:04,538 --> 00:04:05,605
If not... oh, right.

57
00:04:05,605 --> 00:04:07,005
Hasn't your stab wound split open yet?

58
00:04:07,005 --> 00:04:08,438
Should I open it up again for you?

59
00:04:08,438 --> 00:04:10,672
Hey, hey!

60
00:04:10,672 --> 00:04:14,005
Wow, you're really
repaying kindness like this?

61
00:04:14,005 --> 00:04:16,938
Anyway, cover it up!
Just be vague about it, okay?

62
00:04:16,938 --> 00:04:18,238
You're good at that. I'm off!

63
00:04:18,238 --> 00:04:19,672
Cover what up?

64
00:04:19,672 --> 00:04:20,705
Just cover that up!

65
00:04:20,705 --> 00:04:22,305
Hey, Tae Joo!

66
00:04:46,672 --> 00:04:49,172
So what are you going to announce today?

67
00:04:49,172 --> 00:04:51,605
Have you found the serial killer?

68
00:04:59,705 --> 00:05:01,672
We have identified

69
00:05:01,672 --> 00:05:05,972
a prime suspect in the seven murder cases
that have occurred in Kangseng

70
00:05:05,972 --> 00:05:09,205
over the past two years, but...

71
00:05:09,205 --> 00:05:10,972
- "But"?
- "But"?

72
00:05:10,972 --> 00:05:13,972
Is he a prime suspect or not?

73
00:05:18,938 --> 00:05:20,705
Father!

74
00:05:29,005 --> 00:05:31,538
[Bang Kyung Moon Clinic]

75
00:05:31,538 --> 00:05:33,205
Drop by sometime.

76
00:05:33,205 --> 00:05:35,105
This old man gets lonely.

77
00:05:35,105 --> 00:05:37,505
I know you're even busier than I am.

78
00:05:38,705 --> 00:05:40,738
There must be a patient named Lee Ki Hwan.

79
00:05:40,738 --> 00:05:42,038
Let me see the list.

80
00:05:42,038 --> 00:05:45,338
- Just a moment.
- Isn't that Detective Kang?

81
00:05:45,338 --> 00:05:47,005
- Detective?
- Yeah.

82
00:05:47,005 --> 00:05:49,838
The detective in charge of
the serial murders.

83
00:05:52,772 --> 00:05:55,305
Please introduce me to him.

84
00:05:55,305 --> 00:05:56,872
Huh?

85
00:05:56,872 --> 00:05:58,372
[Dr. Jo Yun Seok
from Korea Atomic Energy Research Institute]

86
00:05:58,372 --> 00:06:00,372
I'm Jo Yun Seok.

87
00:06:01,005 --> 00:06:02,638
Please have a seat.

88
00:06:04,738 --> 00:06:08,072
Why is someone from the nuclear
research institute looking for me?

89
00:06:08,072 --> 00:06:11,972
I was hoping to explain some
scientific methods that could help

90
00:06:11,972 --> 00:06:13,705
narrow down the suspects.

91
00:06:13,705 --> 00:06:15,561
Is there such a method?

92
00:06:16,905 --> 00:06:20,805
It's a method called 'radioisotope analysis.'

93
00:06:20,805 --> 00:06:22,338
What can you do with that?

94
00:06:22,338 --> 00:06:24,805
Just like our fingerprints are all different,

95
00:06:24,805 --> 00:06:29,205
the elemental composition of human hair
also varies from person to person.

96
00:06:29,205 --> 00:06:31,005
So you're saying

97
00:06:31,005 --> 00:06:34,205
you can irradiate the suspect's
and the killer's hair,

98
00:06:34,205 --> 00:06:39,372
and based on the elements released,
determine if they're the same person?

99
00:06:39,372 --> 00:06:44,972
Yes, based on the results, we might infer
their occupation or living environment.

100
00:06:46,838 --> 00:06:49,472
Have you ever identified
a suspect using this method?

101
00:06:49,472 --> 00:06:50,772
No.

102
00:06:50,772 --> 00:06:53,505
Has it ever been accepted
as evidence in court?

103
00:06:54,238 --> 00:06:56,772
Well, not yet.

104
00:06:58,038 --> 00:07:01,305
Everything has a first time, doesn't it?

105
00:07:01,305 --> 00:07:02,633
- A first time...
- Today,

106
00:07:02,633 --> 00:07:05,138
the Kangseng Branch
of the Muwon District Prosecutors' Office

107
00:07:05,138 --> 00:07:09,638
announced they have identified
a serial killer behind seven murders of women

108
00:07:09,638 --> 00:07:11,872
over the past two years.

109
00:07:11,872 --> 00:07:17,205
The suspect is a man in his 20s,
surnamed Lee, who lives in Kangseng

110
00:07:17,205 --> 00:07:19,772
and runs a bookstore.

111
00:07:19,772 --> 00:07:23,738
The murder of a middle school girl
on the 22nd

112
00:07:23,738 --> 00:07:26,838
has also been confirmed as his doing.

113
00:07:26,838 --> 00:07:28,438
Looks like you don't need my proposal.

114
00:07:28,438 --> 00:07:29,472
The crime scene is

115
00:07:29,472 --> 00:07:32,105
- That darn lunatic.
- around Jangseong village.

116
00:07:32,105 --> 00:07:37,272
He targeted women who were
usually alone on their way home,

117
00:07:37,272 --> 00:07:40,238
abducted them,
restrained their hands and feet

118
00:07:40,238 --> 00:07:43,205
to prevent resistance,
sexually assaulted them,

119
00:07:43,205 --> 00:07:47,238
and then brutally murdered them.

120
00:07:47,938 --> 00:07:49,488
As the suspect

121
00:07:49,488 --> 00:07:51,372
continues to kill,

122
00:07:51,372 --> 00:07:53,972
the interval between crimes has decreased,

123
00:07:53,972 --> 00:07:56,272
and bodies were also
found around the village...

124
00:07:56,272 --> 00:07:57,705
Mother, please stay strong...

125
00:07:57,705 --> 00:08:00,272
Take it away!

126
00:08:00,272 --> 00:08:02,872
What should I do?

127
00:08:04,105 --> 00:08:08,672
We have clearly classified this case
as a serial murder case,

128
00:08:08,672 --> 00:08:11,805
and will conduct a thorough investigation
to determine the full facts,

129
00:08:11,805 --> 00:08:14,338
ensure such incidents do not happen again,

130
00:08:14,338 --> 00:08:19,805
and remain fully committed
to justice and accountability.

131
00:08:19,805 --> 00:08:22,972
The prosecution has placed the suspect,
Mr. Lee, on a public wanted list

132
00:08:22,972 --> 00:08:26,805
and stated they will do their utmost
to apprehend him quickly.

133
00:08:26,805 --> 00:08:29,938
Thus, attention is now focused on
whether this will bring an end

134
00:08:29,938 --> 00:08:33,172
to the serial murder case
that has left Kangseng in fear

135
00:08:33,172 --> 00:08:35,738
over the past two years.

136
00:08:35,738 --> 00:08:39,305
This has been Reporter Kim Ji Hun from KBS.

137
00:08:45,105 --> 00:08:47,038
It's ginger tea.

138
00:08:56,172 --> 00:08:59,305
The aroma is nice.

139
00:09:00,438 --> 00:09:03,538
What brings you here?
You must be busy with election preparation.

140
00:09:03,538 --> 00:09:08,138
Let's finalize your marriage arrangement
with Chairman Kim soon.

141
00:09:09,272 --> 00:09:11,705
That can wait until after the election.

142
00:09:11,705 --> 00:09:14,205
How do you know
how the election will turn out?

143
00:09:14,205 --> 00:09:17,438
We need to set a date in advance,
so there's no backing out.

144
00:09:23,472 --> 00:09:27,172
So you found the serial killer?

145
00:09:27,172 --> 00:09:28,772
Yes.

146
00:09:29,472 --> 00:09:31,072
You've worked hard.

147
00:09:36,938 --> 00:09:38,605
Father.

148
00:09:41,172 --> 00:09:43,705
Cha Si Young, you...

149
00:09:46,205 --> 00:09:47,772
Detective Kang!

150
00:09:47,772 --> 00:09:50,605
How rude of you! I have a guest here.

151
00:09:50,605 --> 00:09:53,638
I don't have time
to take a number and wait, sir.

152
00:09:53,638 --> 00:09:55,138
Could I borrow Prosecutor Cha?

153
00:09:55,138 --> 00:09:57,805
Alright, I understand.
Let's talk later, okay?

154
00:09:57,805 --> 00:10:00,265
If official business is urgent,

155
00:10:00,265 --> 00:10:02,038
this old man should step aside.

156
00:10:02,038 --> 00:10:05,105
No, Father, you don't have to do that.

157
00:10:05,105 --> 00:10:06,938
- Just a moment...
- You don't need to come out.

158
00:10:09,972 --> 00:10:11,572
Wait.

159
00:10:15,738 --> 00:10:18,305
Have we met somewhere before?

160
00:10:27,938 --> 00:10:30,538
I don't think so.

161
00:10:31,905 --> 00:10:34,105
I must be mistaken.

162
00:10:36,172 --> 00:10:37,972
I'll call you.

163
00:10:37,972 --> 00:10:39,572
Wait, Father...

164
00:10:45,091 --> 00:10:46,872
[An Upright Republic of Korea]

165
00:10:46,872 --> 00:10:48,672
Hey!

166
00:10:48,672 --> 00:10:50,838
What's up with the press conference?

167
00:10:50,838 --> 00:10:53,672
I told you we need to investigate further.

168
00:10:53,672 --> 00:10:57,238
I thought about it too.

169
00:10:57,238 --> 00:10:59,238
The date on that photo of Lee Ki Beom.

170
00:10:59,238 --> 00:11:03,372
It's the date of Choi In Sook's
disappearance, not her death.

171
00:11:03,372 --> 00:11:07,405
The body was too decomposed
to determine the exact time of death.

172
00:11:07,405 --> 00:11:09,072
- What are you saying...
- And also,

173
00:11:09,072 --> 00:11:13,105
like her mother said,
Choi In Sook might have run away.

174
00:11:13,105 --> 00:11:15,105
There are many possibilities.

175
00:11:15,872 --> 00:11:17,672
What's your excuse for this right now?

176
00:11:17,672 --> 00:11:19,572
Why are you being
so unreasonable all of a sudden?

177
00:11:19,572 --> 00:11:21,738
Who's being unreasonable right now?

178
00:11:21,738 --> 00:11:23,672
Is it because of Sun Young?

179
00:11:25,938 --> 00:11:27,905
What do you mean by that?

180
00:11:28,538 --> 00:11:31,038
Sun Young is pregnant
with Lee Ki Beom's child, right?

181
00:11:32,872 --> 00:11:35,738
Jeez... I knew it.

182
00:11:35,738 --> 00:11:39,938
Back at Lee Ki Beom's place,
I wondered if it might be morning sickness.

183
00:11:41,513 --> 00:11:44,538
What is Sun Young going to do now?

184
00:11:44,538 --> 00:11:47,005
Why are you even bringing her up now?

185
00:11:47,005 --> 00:11:48,238
Hey.

186
00:11:48,238 --> 00:11:52,305
You want to save him because he's the father
of your future niece or nephew, don't you?

187
00:11:52,305 --> 00:11:53,872
What are you even talking about?

188
00:11:53,872 --> 00:11:57,438
If not him, then is there
another suspect besides Lee Ki Beom?

189
00:11:57,438 --> 00:11:59,072
That's...

190
00:12:00,738 --> 00:12:04,138
It's certain the suspect is
someone around Lee Ki Beom.

191
00:12:04,138 --> 00:12:05,738
So I'll widen the investigation...

192
00:12:05,738 --> 00:12:08,505
Bring me the real killer!

193
00:12:08,505 --> 00:12:11,505
Bring me evidence and convince me, you punk!

194
00:12:12,438 --> 00:12:15,205
That's the order of things, Tae Joo!

195
00:12:21,872 --> 00:12:23,972
You darn commie punk!

196
00:12:23,972 --> 00:12:27,305
[Capital 1-2]
Spill it quick, you punk!

197
00:12:27,305 --> 00:12:30,272
Let's end this today.

198
00:12:33,305 --> 00:12:37,838
I've treated you nicely all this time.

199
00:12:37,838 --> 00:12:39,572
Let's start again.

200
00:12:42,272 --> 00:12:46,505
Darn it, it's driving me crazy.

201
00:12:47,305 --> 00:12:50,905
I told you to bring him in, not beat him up!

202
00:12:50,905 --> 00:12:52,905
I'm sorry, Prosecutor Cha.

203
00:12:53,805 --> 00:12:55,172
Take that out of his mouth.

204
00:12:55,172 --> 00:12:56,805
Yes, sir!

205
00:13:06,972 --> 00:13:09,272
So, your bookstore has a lot of things?

206
00:13:10,105 --> 00:13:11,272
You heard, right?

207
00:13:11,272 --> 00:13:13,772
What was found in your bookstore?

208
00:13:13,772 --> 00:13:15,872
Communist books were found,

209
00:13:15,872 --> 00:13:18,205
and a victim's purse too.

210
00:13:18,905 --> 00:13:21,172
It's like a treasure trove, huh?

211
00:13:24,038 --> 00:13:26,305
I didn't do anything.

212
00:13:28,105 --> 00:13:29,805
What did you say?

213
00:13:30,772 --> 00:13:32,538
Say that again.

214
00:13:33,305 --> 00:13:35,238
It wasn't me.

215
00:13:38,672 --> 00:13:40,738
He might be telling the truth.

216
00:13:41,905 --> 00:13:42,972
Maybe it's not him!

217
00:13:42,972 --> 00:13:44,972
No,

218
00:13:44,972 --> 00:13:46,005
that can't be.

219
00:13:46,005 --> 00:13:47,938
Look at his eyes!

220
00:13:47,938 --> 00:13:50,905
Do they look like the eyes of a liar?

221
00:13:50,905 --> 00:13:55,838
Jeez, this guy isn't the serial killer.

222
00:13:55,838 --> 00:13:58,372
He's just a commie!

223
00:14:00,038 --> 00:14:02,872
Then who is the suspect, Mr. Cha?

224
00:14:02,872 --> 00:14:05,769
It must be his brother! The bookstore
belongs to his brother, right?

225
00:14:08,238 --> 00:14:09,338
That makes sense.

226
00:14:09,338 --> 00:14:14,272
Good grief, how did your mother
raise her children like this?

227
00:14:14,272 --> 00:14:18,038
One's a serial killer,
and the other's a commie.

228
00:14:18,038 --> 00:14:20,472
In that case, your mother's
the root of it all, you know.

229
00:14:20,472 --> 00:14:22,205
Giving birth to monsters like you...

230
00:14:22,205 --> 00:14:25,372
Shut up! Stop talking nonsense!

231
00:14:26,005 --> 00:14:30,472
Calm down and keep this in mind.

232
00:14:30,472 --> 00:14:34,672
This is how the world
will see your mother from now on.

233
00:14:38,472 --> 00:14:40,972
What are you waiting for?
Why aren't you bringing in his brother?

234
00:14:40,972 --> 00:14:43,072
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

235
00:14:43,072 --> 00:14:46,005
No, not my brother!

236
00:14:46,005 --> 00:14:48,272
My brother isn't that kind of person!

237
00:14:48,272 --> 00:14:49,972
Then who is it?

238
00:15:03,872 --> 00:15:05,605
Tell me who it is.

239
00:15:07,305 --> 00:15:08,938
Promise me,

240
00:15:10,605 --> 00:15:12,472
if I confess,

241
00:15:13,638 --> 00:15:16,072
you won't touch my family.

242
00:15:19,072 --> 00:15:22,105
This punk is threatening a prosecutor, huh?

243
00:15:22,105 --> 00:15:23,205
Promise me!

244
00:15:23,205 --> 00:15:25,005
You punk.

245
00:15:28,172 --> 00:15:32,338
In return, there's something
you have to promise me too.

246
00:15:35,038 --> 00:15:38,072
[Korea Atomic Energy Research Institute]

247
00:15:39,672 --> 00:15:41,405
Oh, hello.

248
00:15:41,405 --> 00:15:43,105
Welcome.

249
00:15:44,638 --> 00:15:46,409
Sorry,

250
00:15:46,409 --> 00:15:50,372
but to be honest, I didn't come here
because I trust your test.

251
00:15:51,038 --> 00:15:53,065
I came here

252
00:15:53,065 --> 00:15:54,505
simply because I'm at a loss,

253
00:15:54,505 --> 00:15:57,872
hoping I might get lucky and find something.

254
00:15:57,872 --> 00:16:01,772
Yes, I understand what you mean.

255
00:16:02,738 --> 00:16:04,838
This is the suspect's hair.

256
00:16:04,838 --> 00:16:06,572
Please analyze it.

257
00:16:15,405 --> 00:16:17,072
If you look here,

258
00:16:17,072 --> 00:16:19,625
[Radioactive Isotope Analysis Report]
compared to average, titanium, sodium,

259
00:16:19,625 --> 00:16:21,572
and chlorine are significantly higher.

260
00:16:21,572 --> 00:16:24,505
Is there a special reason for that?

261
00:16:24,505 --> 00:16:26,305
High titanium levels would mean

262
00:16:26,305 --> 00:16:29,772
the person has been exposed
to a titanium-rich environment.

263
00:16:29,772 --> 00:16:34,305
He could be a worker in a factory
that handles alloys or welding.

264
00:16:35,838 --> 00:16:38,072
What about sodium and chlorine?

265
00:16:38,072 --> 00:16:41,305
Those are the main components of sweat.

266
00:16:41,305 --> 00:16:43,838
He's likely someone who sweats a lot.

267
00:16:44,838 --> 00:16:48,105
So you're saying the killer could be

268
00:16:48,105 --> 00:16:49,929
a factory worker

269
00:16:49,929 --> 00:16:53,705
who's constantly
drenched in sweat, is that it?

270
00:16:53,705 --> 00:16:55,305
Probably.

271
00:16:57,905 --> 00:17:01,738
[Occupation: factory worker]

272
00:17:03,538 --> 00:17:06,072
Go stay at your parents' for a while.

273
00:17:06,072 --> 00:17:11,005
But will you and your mother be okay?

274
00:17:11,005 --> 00:17:12,438
You know how stubborn my mother is.

275
00:17:12,438 --> 00:17:15,205
She's not the type to
leave Ki Beom alone and go somewhere.

276
00:17:18,872 --> 00:17:20,205
Please take care of her.

277
00:17:20,205 --> 00:17:22,205
Don't worry about us, Ki Hwan.

278
00:17:47,338 --> 00:17:53,638
[Murderer, get out]

279
00:18:07,715 --> 00:18:11,235
[Korean Novel]

280
00:18:17,172 --> 00:18:24,172
[Kangseng Bookstore]

281
00:18:30,738 --> 00:18:32,338
Tae Joo!

282
00:18:34,072 --> 00:18:38,105
Where have you been?
Hurry up and clean this up.

283
00:18:38,105 --> 00:18:39,805
Oh, okay.

284
00:18:48,805 --> 00:18:53,905
I don't know how they found out,
but both the house and bookstore are a mess.

285
00:18:57,605 --> 00:18:59,905
How is your mother doing?

286
00:18:59,905 --> 00:19:01,872
She's been laid up in bed
from the shock, of course.

287
00:19:01,872 --> 00:19:05,738
I told her to stay at a relative's,
but she won't listen.

288
00:19:10,405 --> 00:19:13,005
Lee Ki Hwan isn't type B.

289
00:19:13,005 --> 00:19:15,005
He is type AB.

290
00:19:17,472 --> 00:19:21,038
[Lee Ki Hwan, Type AB]

291
00:19:32,472 --> 00:19:35,338
Ki Hwan, actually...

292
00:19:36,305 --> 00:19:38,505
What is it?

293
00:19:38,505 --> 00:19:40,838
Oh my, you should be careful.

294
00:19:40,838 --> 00:19:42,438
It's just a small cut.

295
00:19:42,438 --> 00:19:43,738
It's not small at all. Jeez.

296
00:19:43,738 --> 00:19:45,505
Hold still. It's bleeding a lot.

297
00:19:45,505 --> 00:19:47,172
- No, I'm fine.
- Press on it.

298
00:19:55,572 --> 00:19:57,205
What are you doing?

299
00:20:01,272 --> 00:20:03,472
What's with that blood?

300
00:20:05,872 --> 00:20:07,705
What is this?

301
00:20:11,205 --> 00:20:12,672
Ji Won, hey!

302
00:20:12,672 --> 00:20:14,605
Ji Won, I'll explain everything.

303
00:20:14,605 --> 00:20:16,038
What were you going to do
with Ki Hwan's blood?

304
00:20:16,038 --> 00:20:18,072
Are you trying to check
his blood type or something?

305
00:20:18,072 --> 00:20:20,938
- This is a misunderstanding.
- Misunderstanding?

306
00:20:20,938 --> 00:20:24,538
Ki Beom wasn't enough, and now it's Ki Hwan?

307
00:20:24,538 --> 00:20:27,238
What's the evidence this time? What is it?

308
00:20:27,238 --> 00:20:29,738
Did you find evidence in the bookstore?

309
00:20:32,438 --> 00:20:34,038
The purse?

310
00:20:38,572 --> 00:20:40,238
Is that it?

311
00:20:41,238 --> 00:20:44,405
You're suspecting me because of that?

312
00:20:44,405 --> 00:20:47,438
Purse? What purse?

313
00:20:49,872 --> 00:20:52,238
Tae Joo, is that true?

314
00:20:55,572 --> 00:20:57,225
So you

315
00:20:57,225 --> 00:21:00,138
really came for that,
to find out my blood type?

316
00:21:00,905 --> 00:21:04,305
You could have just asked. I can tell you.

317
00:21:04,305 --> 00:21:05,905
I'm type AB.

318
00:21:06,705 --> 00:21:09,872
If you don't believe me,
take this and get it tested.

319
00:21:10,538 --> 00:21:12,238
Enough, man.

320
00:21:14,772 --> 00:21:16,605
Yeah, honestly,

321
00:21:17,805 --> 00:21:19,672
I suspected you.

322
00:21:20,605 --> 00:21:22,738
But not anymore, though.

323
00:21:27,605 --> 00:21:30,672
I'm sorry, I'm really...

324
00:21:34,672 --> 00:21:36,472
- Are you okay?
- Are you okay?

325
00:21:37,138 --> 00:21:38,305
Are you alright?

326
00:21:38,305 --> 00:21:39,472
- Let me see.
- Let me see.

327
00:21:39,472 --> 00:21:41,138
- Let me see.
- Jeez.

328
00:21:41,138 --> 00:21:42,938
Let me see, hurry.

329
00:21:45,205 --> 00:21:48,172
How did the victim's belonging get here?

330
00:21:48,172 --> 00:21:51,305
Unless someone deliberately placed it here.

331
00:21:51,305 --> 00:21:55,172
I don't know where things went wrong, either.

332
00:21:57,505 --> 00:22:00,038
We need to catch the real killer,
so Ki Beom can clear his name.

333
00:22:00,038 --> 00:22:01,638
That's the situation now.

334
00:22:03,038 --> 00:22:05,738
That punk is definitely close to Ki Beom.

335
00:22:06,505 --> 00:22:10,372
Has Ki Beom been hanging out
with shady people?

336
00:22:10,372 --> 00:22:11,405
Like someone with a criminal record...

337
00:22:11,405 --> 00:22:15,505
No. They are all people
he's known since childhood.

338
00:22:17,638 --> 00:22:22,638
He could be a worker in a factory
that handles alloys or welding.

339
00:22:22,638 --> 00:22:24,672
Any friend working at a factory?

340
00:22:24,672 --> 00:22:25,972
Yeah, there is one.

341
00:22:25,972 --> 00:22:27,605
Why the factory?

342
00:22:29,505 --> 00:22:30,838
Where is it?

343
00:22:30,838 --> 00:22:32,672
Ilwon Industries.

344
00:22:38,005 --> 00:22:40,905
[Testing Facility]
Excuse me, is there a guy named Jung Soo?

345
00:22:40,905 --> 00:22:42,538
Over there.

346
00:23:19,105 --> 00:23:21,805
[Ilwon Industries]

347
00:23:21,805 --> 00:23:23,338
Here it is.

348
00:23:23,338 --> 00:23:25,238
Yes, thank you.

349
00:23:26,038 --> 00:23:30,805
[Lee Jung Soo, Type O]

350
00:23:31,672 --> 00:23:33,405
Type O...

351
00:23:34,281 --> 00:23:35,438
They're here!

352
00:23:35,438 --> 00:23:36,738
What was your motive?

353
00:23:36,738 --> 00:23:39,505
Is it true you chased down and murdered
a schoolgirl who visited the bookstore?

354
00:23:39,505 --> 00:23:41,038
Please move aside.

355
00:23:41,038 --> 00:23:44,472
Are you the real killer
in the serial murder case?

356
00:23:46,472 --> 00:23:48,472
Answer me!

357
00:23:49,838 --> 00:23:51,905
Just say one thing.

358
00:23:52,705 --> 00:23:54,805
He is not saying anything.

359
00:23:55,971 --> 00:23:57,578
Did you get anything?

360
00:23:57,578 --> 00:23:59,435
- No, no...
- Jeez.

361
00:24:00,472 --> 00:24:03,738
How does it feel? Relieving, isn't it?

362
00:24:03,738 --> 00:24:05,938
That's what confession is like.

363
00:24:08,605 --> 00:24:10,572
Detective Kang, good timing.

364
00:24:10,572 --> 00:24:12,938
Lee Ki Beom just confessed to everything.

365
00:24:12,938 --> 00:24:14,569
[Security Interview Room]
What?

366
00:24:14,569 --> 00:24:15,738
Already?

367
00:24:15,738 --> 00:24:19,038
This little rat finally realized
he couldn't escape

368
00:24:19,038 --> 00:24:21,638
and spilled everything right away.

369
00:24:21,638 --> 00:24:22,772
I need to talk to him for a moment.

370
00:24:22,772 --> 00:24:23,972
No way, man.

371
00:24:23,972 --> 00:24:25,205
Just a minute is enough.

372
00:24:25,205 --> 00:24:26,805
Detective Do,

373
00:24:26,805 --> 00:24:28,838
let's step outside for a smoke.

374
00:24:28,838 --> 00:24:31,872
Okay, let's go.

375
00:24:33,438 --> 00:24:36,038
Oh, wait a second.

376
00:24:46,738 --> 00:24:48,338
Ki Beom.

377
00:24:50,338 --> 00:24:52,205
What happened?

378
00:24:54,172 --> 00:24:56,105
It's exactly as you heard.

379
00:25:00,638 --> 00:25:02,805
Was it really you?

380
00:25:08,638 --> 00:25:10,238
Answer me!

381
00:25:10,238 --> 00:25:12,205
Was it really you?

382
00:25:14,372 --> 00:25:16,005
Yes.

383
00:25:18,755 --> 00:25:19,881
What?

384
00:25:20,572 --> 00:25:22,505
Why would someone who's been
hiding so desperately

385
00:25:22,505 --> 00:25:25,372
suddenly confess so easily?

386
00:25:25,372 --> 00:25:28,305
In return, there's something
you have to promise me too.

387
00:25:28,305 --> 00:25:33,638
Don't bring up being detained
or anything like that.

388
00:25:34,505 --> 00:25:36,905
I heard evidence was found
at the bookstore, right?

389
00:25:36,905 --> 00:25:40,872
If I kept denying it, my brother
would inevitably be suspected.

390
00:25:41,905 --> 00:25:43,593
How could I

391
00:25:43,593 --> 00:25:45,405
do that to my family?

392
00:25:46,538 --> 00:25:52,072
You care so much about your family,
but you killed victims so brutally?

393
00:25:52,072 --> 00:25:55,272
They all had precious families too.

394
00:25:55,272 --> 00:25:57,638
But they aren't my family.

395
00:26:00,372 --> 00:26:02,238
So you...

396
00:26:02,238 --> 00:26:04,372
So you...

397
00:26:04,372 --> 00:26:08,457
So you tried to kill Sun Young too? Huh?

398
00:26:14,205 --> 00:26:18,345
Are you really the Ki Beom I knew?

399
00:26:37,289 --> 00:26:38,665
Darn it!

400
00:26:43,438 --> 00:26:45,072
Tae Joo.

401
00:26:46,005 --> 00:26:47,172
What happened?

402
00:26:47,172 --> 00:26:49,005
What did Ki Beom say?

403
00:26:53,038 --> 00:26:56,272
Ki Beom has confessed.

404
00:27:00,205 --> 00:27:02,305
Did you hit him?

405
00:27:02,305 --> 00:27:06,205
- What?
- You beat a false confession out of him!

406
00:27:07,838 --> 00:27:10,538
Ki Beom was brought in today.

407
00:27:10,538 --> 00:27:12,772
He confessed as soon as he arrived.

408
00:27:12,772 --> 00:27:15,238
That punk... Ki Beom is the killer!

409
00:27:15,238 --> 00:27:17,638
No! It's not true!

410
00:27:17,638 --> 00:27:19,405
He admitted it himself!

411
00:27:19,405 --> 00:27:21,005
He said he did it himself!

412
00:27:21,005 --> 00:27:24,605
You, me, all of us, we've all
been fooled by him this whole time!

413
00:27:24,605 --> 00:27:25,672
Get a grip!

414
00:27:25,672 --> 00:27:26,738
No...

415
00:27:26,738 --> 00:27:29,038
Don't cry. Why are you crying?

416
00:27:29,838 --> 00:27:31,672
No.

417
00:27:32,777 --> 00:27:35,638
- Sun Young.
- No...

418
00:27:37,372 --> 00:27:39,505
I'll find a hospital.

419
00:27:40,305 --> 00:27:42,005
Just get an abortion first.

420
00:27:46,505 --> 00:27:48,246
It's okay.

421
00:27:51,872 --> 00:27:53,838
- Give me a cigarette, please.
- Okay.

422
00:27:57,805 --> 00:28:00,872
[Kangseng Serial Killer Arrested,
Mr. Lee, 20s, Bookstore Owner]

423
00:28:00,872 --> 00:28:05,138
They caught the suspect even before
a special investigation team was formed?

424
00:28:05,138 --> 00:28:06,838
The newly assigned officers are in chaos.

425
00:28:06,838 --> 00:28:08,105
[Prosecutor Cha, second son of Candidate Cha]
They're asking if they should still come.

426
00:28:08,105 --> 00:28:10,938
What is this, all show and no substance?

427
00:28:17,772 --> 00:28:20,905
Hold off the assignments for those
who haven't been dispatched yet,

428
00:28:20,905 --> 00:28:23,038
and form the team as planned with the rest.

429
00:28:23,038 --> 00:28:26,272
What? What are you planning to do?

430
00:28:30,305 --> 00:28:31,605
It'll only take a moment.

431
00:28:31,605 --> 00:28:34,838
I have something important I need to say.

432
00:28:34,838 --> 00:28:38,038
It's no use asking me, Ms. Kang.

433
00:28:43,038 --> 00:28:44,905
What's going on?

434
00:28:47,138 --> 00:28:50,838
I... I have a favor to ask.

435
00:28:57,699 --> 00:29:00,005
[Security Interview Room]

436
00:29:00,005 --> 00:29:02,038
Sun Young.

437
00:29:02,038 --> 00:29:03,238
You have 5 minutes.

438
00:29:03,238 --> 00:29:04,338
I'll be outside.

439
00:29:04,338 --> 00:29:06,105
Thank you.

440
00:29:10,138 --> 00:29:11,805
Ki Beom.

441
00:29:15,572 --> 00:29:16,572
What happened?

442
00:29:16,572 --> 00:29:18,772
I asked the prosecutor in charge.

443
00:29:20,205 --> 00:29:21,805
Sun Young...

444
00:29:24,772 --> 00:29:26,472
Don't get involved with him.

445
00:29:26,472 --> 00:29:28,972
Don't even ask him for favors like this.

446
00:29:28,972 --> 00:29:30,938
Is that what matters right now?

447
00:29:30,938 --> 00:29:33,072
Why did you admit something you didn't do?

448
00:29:33,872 --> 00:29:36,238
That wasn't you!

449
00:29:39,372 --> 00:29:41,638
How can you smile at a time like this?

450
00:29:43,405 --> 00:29:45,838
You still believe me now?

451
00:29:45,838 --> 00:29:48,772
Even when I say I'm a murderer,

452
00:29:49,405 --> 00:29:51,038
you still trust me?

453
00:30:02,072 --> 00:30:03,672
Ki Beom.

454
00:30:11,172 --> 00:30:13,405
We're having a child.

455
00:30:16,872 --> 00:30:18,605
What?

456
00:30:20,872 --> 00:30:26,272
I don't know why you're lying, but...

457
00:30:29,705 --> 00:30:33,105
if you think of our unborn child,

458
00:30:34,538 --> 00:30:38,072
if you're not ashamed before our child,

459
00:30:39,672 --> 00:30:41,705
fight until the end.

460
00:30:42,905 --> 00:30:44,605
Fight

461
00:30:45,338 --> 00:30:47,172
and make sure to come back.

462
00:30:49,738 --> 00:30:52,005
Please stay by our side.

463
00:30:52,005 --> 00:30:53,605
Okay?

464
00:31:09,205 --> 00:31:11,338
Ki Beom.

465
00:31:11,338 --> 00:31:13,172
I'll wait for you.

466
00:31:19,272 --> 00:31:20,872
Sun Young...

467
00:31:45,872 --> 00:31:47,605
Aren't you writing the article?

468
00:31:47,605 --> 00:31:49,205
What?

469
00:31:52,905 --> 00:31:54,938
Excuse me for a moment.

470
00:31:56,205 --> 00:31:59,372
So? What did you do next?

471
00:32:00,505 --> 00:32:02,538
After I followed her,

472
00:32:03,505 --> 00:32:05,097
I threatened her

473
00:32:05,097 --> 00:32:06,872
with a knife.

474
00:32:06,872 --> 00:32:08,605
And then?

475
00:32:12,872 --> 00:32:14,985
I said

476
00:32:14,985 --> 00:32:16,772
I would kill her if she didn't come with me.

477
00:32:17,891 --> 00:32:19,182
Right.

478
00:32:21,605 --> 00:32:25,872
The voice is similar, but I'm not sure.

479
00:32:26,838 --> 00:32:29,705
"The voice is similar"?

480
00:32:30,338 --> 00:32:32,705
That's enough.

481
00:32:32,705 --> 00:32:34,805
Alright, you can take this back now.

482
00:32:39,105 --> 00:32:41,972
Even so, you've had a hard time
coming all this way.

483
00:32:41,972 --> 00:32:43,605
Huh?

484
00:32:44,505 --> 00:32:46,272
This isn't mine.

485
00:32:46,272 --> 00:32:48,972
It must have gotten mixed in by mistake.

486
00:32:48,972 --> 00:32:50,638
Please throw that away.

487
00:33:02,372 --> 00:33:04,938
Excuse me, Ms. Park Ae Sook?

488
00:33:06,238 --> 00:33:07,338
Who are you?

489
00:33:07,338 --> 00:33:09,305
Well...

490
00:33:09,305 --> 00:33:12,505
I'm Seo Ji Won, a reporter
from Kangseng Daily.

491
00:33:19,972 --> 00:33:23,372
Do any of these people look familiar?

492
00:33:29,172 --> 00:33:31,172
I don't recognize any of them.

493
00:33:31,172 --> 00:33:33,505
Who are they?

494
00:33:33,505 --> 00:33:38,005
Let's say they are people who frequented
the bookstore where your purse was found.

495
00:33:41,838 --> 00:33:44,505
Wasn't the suspect already caught?

496
00:33:46,705 --> 00:33:49,038
Doesn't it feel strange?

497
00:33:49,038 --> 00:33:51,272
Your ID was inside the purse.

498
00:33:51,272 --> 00:33:53,972
If I were the culprit,

499
00:33:53,972 --> 00:33:59,038
I think I'd leave that purse
in front of your house, as a warning.

500
00:33:59,038 --> 00:34:02,738
But why did the culprit
leave it at the bookstore?

501
00:34:06,138 --> 00:34:09,638
I tend to be suspicious,
so please understand.

502
00:34:15,705 --> 00:34:17,338
Actually,

503
00:34:18,738 --> 00:34:20,713
I just found this

504
00:34:20,713 --> 00:34:22,205
inside the purse.

505
00:34:22,205 --> 00:34:24,405
[Pig Café]

506
00:34:24,405 --> 00:34:26,605
It's not mine.

507
00:34:33,443 --> 00:34:35,002
[2nd Floor Information]

508
00:34:38,138 --> 00:34:39,872
Dad!

509
00:34:43,272 --> 00:34:45,072
I'm sorry!

510
00:34:46,697 --> 00:34:51,305
Whenever my kid sees an adult man,
he thinks it's his dad.

511
00:34:51,305 --> 00:34:54,205
Hae Jun, let's go.

512
00:34:56,272 --> 00:34:58,472
What are you waiting for? Let's go.

513
00:35:11,572 --> 00:35:13,672
Is Lee Ki Beom's statement almost done?

514
00:35:13,672 --> 00:35:15,538
Yes, would you like to see it?

515
00:35:15,538 --> 00:35:17,138
Why would I?

516
00:35:25,405 --> 00:35:27,572
Did Lee Ki Beom really give this statement?

517
00:35:27,572 --> 00:35:29,638
Yes, why?

518
00:35:29,638 --> 00:35:32,472
It's all information we already know.
And some of it doesn't even match.

519
00:35:32,472 --> 00:35:34,438
What do you mean it doesn't match?

520
00:35:34,438 --> 00:35:38,472
It says he was already wearing a handkerchief
when he abducted Kim Mi Yeon, right?

521
00:35:38,472 --> 00:35:40,205
It doesn't match.

522
00:35:40,972 --> 00:35:45,905
According to Kim Mi Yeon, the suspect
only had his hat pulled low at that time.

523
00:35:45,905 --> 00:35:48,938
He put on the handkerchief afterward,
before attacking Ji Won.

524
00:35:48,938 --> 00:35:51,172
Could he have been confused? Or maybe...

525
00:35:58,038 --> 00:35:59,972
What are you talking about, Ki Beom?

526
00:35:59,972 --> 00:36:03,605
I won't just write down
whatever you tell me anymore.

527
00:36:09,105 --> 00:36:11,672
You punk!

528
00:36:11,672 --> 00:36:14,838
You haven't been beaten lately,
so life feels easy, huh?

529
00:36:14,838 --> 00:36:16,572
Get up!

530
00:36:16,572 --> 00:36:19,038
This is why someone like you

531
00:36:19,038 --> 00:36:23,505
needs to be beaten every day, you punk!

532
00:36:23,505 --> 00:36:24,937
- What are you doing?
- Detective Kang!

533
00:36:24,937 --> 00:36:27,038
Move aside.

534
00:36:27,038 --> 00:36:28,672
Ki Beom!

535
00:36:28,672 --> 00:36:29,838
Darn it.

536
00:36:29,838 --> 00:36:31,305
Are you alright?

537
00:36:31,305 --> 00:36:33,097
Look at me.

538
00:36:33,772 --> 00:36:35,872
- Ki Beom, are you okay?
- Tae Joo.

539
00:36:35,872 --> 00:36:37,475
Let's go.

540
00:36:41,172 --> 00:36:42,805
What's wrong?

541
00:36:49,172 --> 00:36:50,805
What is this?

542
00:36:51,672 --> 00:36:53,305
This...

543
00:36:54,405 --> 00:36:56,838
These aren't fresh wounds
from just yesterday or today.

544
00:36:56,838 --> 00:36:59,405
When did you get these?

545
00:37:08,072 --> 00:37:12,638
You were lying about
losing Lee Ki Beom from the start, right?

546
00:37:12,638 --> 00:37:17,138
You were secretly imprisoning
and interrogating him all along, right?

547
00:37:18,238 --> 00:37:20,372
What does that matter now?
We caught the suspect.

548
00:37:20,372 --> 00:37:23,138
Illegal arrest!
Unlawful confinement and assault!

549
00:37:23,138 --> 00:37:25,838
Any confession obtained that way is invalid!

550
00:37:25,838 --> 00:37:28,372
If Prosecutor Cha finds out
everything you've done...

551
00:37:38,405 --> 00:37:40,672
So that punk ordered it, huh?

552
00:37:45,438 --> 00:37:48,638
What a double celebration this is.

553
00:37:48,638 --> 00:37:51,072
Prosecutor Cha caught a serial killer,

554
00:37:51,072 --> 00:37:53,705
and your approval ratings have risen.

555
00:37:55,838 --> 00:37:57,472
Exactly,

556
00:37:57,472 --> 00:37:59,672
I'm benefiting from this guy too.

557
00:37:59,672 --> 00:38:02,872
When I heard he had been stabbed,
my heart just sank.

558
00:38:02,872 --> 00:38:06,572
Anyway, you really don't hesitate
to do dangerous things.

559
00:38:06,572 --> 00:38:08,505
If anything like this happens again,

560
00:38:08,505 --> 00:38:11,738
I won't let Hee Jin marry you.

561
00:38:11,738 --> 00:38:12,805
Understood.

562
00:38:12,805 --> 00:38:14,705
Oh my, Dad.

563
00:38:14,705 --> 00:38:17,838
I really admire that side of Si Young.

564
00:38:17,838 --> 00:38:19,138
Oh my, you...

565
00:38:19,138 --> 00:38:20,972
Have you no shame,
right in front of Candidate Cha?

566
00:38:20,972 --> 00:38:24,205
No, it's fine.

567
00:38:24,205 --> 00:38:27,805
Hee Jin is such a sweet girl.

568
00:38:29,138 --> 00:38:31,705
Thank you, Father.

569
00:38:31,705 --> 00:38:33,305
"Father"?

570
00:38:35,305 --> 00:38:37,172
That sounds nice.

571
00:38:37,938 --> 00:38:41,172
It would've been nice
if your wife could have joined us.

572
00:38:41,172 --> 00:38:43,105
She's a bit unwell,

573
00:38:43,105 --> 00:38:45,738
but I'm sure she'll be back on her feet soon.

574
00:38:45,738 --> 00:38:51,772
Keeping talent like this only in Kangseng
would be a national loss, don't you think?

575
00:38:54,272 --> 00:38:56,905
Everyone has their purpose, I guess.

576
00:38:56,905 --> 00:39:01,705
Where there's a will, there's a way.

577
00:39:01,705 --> 00:39:06,705
Oh, how about holding the wedding
right after the election?

578
00:39:07,572 --> 00:39:09,738
That would be good.

579
00:39:12,105 --> 00:39:13,738
Please eat.

580
00:39:26,638 --> 00:39:31,005
Once this case is over,
prepare to move up to Seoul.

581
00:39:31,005 --> 00:39:32,105
Pardon?

582
00:39:32,105 --> 00:39:36,772
You just get ready quietly.
Chairman Kim will handle the rest.

583
00:39:36,772 --> 00:39:41,572
The wedding will be held in Seoul anyway,
so he'll naturally hurry it along.

584
00:39:41,572 --> 00:39:47,238
There's no better occasion
to greet people than family events.

585
00:39:47,238 --> 00:39:51,273
And Chairman Kim isn't the type
to miss such opportunities.

586
00:39:54,338 --> 00:39:55,938
Go home.

587
00:39:57,805 --> 00:40:01,438
Aren't you coming in?
Jun Young is probably waiting.

588
00:40:02,072 --> 00:40:03,972
I'm heading to the office.

589
00:40:12,705 --> 00:40:14,372
That guy.

590
00:40:27,338 --> 00:40:29,638
He has good eyes.

591
00:40:29,638 --> 00:40:33,372
He's ambitious and gutsy, but fearless.

592
00:40:35,105 --> 00:40:37,805
If needed, bring him to Seoul and use him.

593
00:41:03,472 --> 00:41:05,272
What are you doing?

594
00:41:08,572 --> 00:41:11,905
My little sister is sick.
Please give us a ride.

595
00:41:11,905 --> 00:41:13,772
- What?
- He's really...

596
00:41:13,772 --> 00:41:16,972
- Go home now! Hurry!
- Just to the hospital.

597
00:41:16,972 --> 00:41:19,138
Please give us a ride just this once.

598
00:41:21,505 --> 00:41:23,205
Aren't you afraid of me?

599
00:41:23,205 --> 00:41:26,405
I'm more afraid of something
happening to my sister.

600
00:41:32,205 --> 00:41:34,505
Your eyes are really...

601
00:41:39,072 --> 00:41:41,705
Your sister has a good older brother.

602
00:41:58,205 --> 00:42:00,638
Father smiled.

603
00:42:01,838 --> 00:42:03,605
Father...

604
00:42:04,805 --> 00:42:06,538
smiled.

605
00:42:19,772 --> 00:42:21,372
Follow me.

606
00:42:33,438 --> 00:42:37,705
Wow, this place is still
exactly the same as before.

607
00:42:38,772 --> 00:42:41,205
Are we the only ones who've changed?

608
00:42:42,238 --> 00:42:43,872
We...

609
00:42:48,372 --> 00:42:50,405
Darn you!

610
00:42:51,705 --> 00:42:54,772
What? Feeling nostalgic?

611
00:42:54,772 --> 00:42:57,738
Want to go back to the old days and fight?

612
00:42:58,705 --> 00:43:01,405
Hey, you punk!

613
00:43:02,238 --> 00:43:05,283
You punk! You deserve a beating.

614
00:43:07,593 --> 00:43:10,281
Darn it!

615
00:43:21,338 --> 00:43:23,172
What are you doing, you punk!

616
00:43:59,205 --> 00:44:02,538
Jeez, stop it! You lunatic!

617
00:44:14,672 --> 00:44:17,417
This is driving me crazy, seriously.

618
00:44:23,272 --> 00:44:26,872
I'd forgotten for a moment
what kind of punk you are.

619
00:44:26,872 --> 00:44:28,205
Honestly,

620
00:44:28,205 --> 00:44:29,672
no matter what kind of punk you were,

621
00:44:29,672 --> 00:44:32,505
I thought I could overlook everything
because you saved Sun Young.

622
00:44:32,505 --> 00:44:33,672
But no.

623
00:44:33,672 --> 00:44:37,872
You're still the same darn punk
you've always been.

624
00:44:37,872 --> 00:44:40,553
You're no different, you punk!

625
00:44:40,553 --> 00:44:42,772
That look in your eyes, huh?

626
00:44:42,772 --> 00:44:44,438
That darn look!

627
00:44:44,438 --> 00:44:46,205
You don't even know your place, you punk!

628
00:44:46,205 --> 00:44:48,938
You can't even tell where you belong
and where you don't.

629
00:44:48,938 --> 00:44:50,772
You don't even know about hierarchy!

630
00:44:50,772 --> 00:44:52,905
How dare you beat a prosecutor!

631
00:44:52,905 --> 00:44:55,038
What, is being a prosecutor
some kind of privilege?

632
00:44:55,038 --> 00:44:58,372
So being a prosecutor gives you
the right to detain and beat people?

633
00:44:58,372 --> 00:45:02,238
Oh, that is what this is about?

634
00:45:02,238 --> 00:45:03,438
Because of Lee Ki Beom!

635
00:45:03,438 --> 00:45:05,705
You're making such a big fuss over just him?

636
00:45:05,705 --> 00:45:09,405
- "Just him"?
- You even admitted that you were wrong!

637
00:45:09,405 --> 00:45:13,238
Well, no matter the means,
this time I'm right.

638
00:45:16,438 --> 00:45:19,105
How come you never learn?

639
00:45:19,105 --> 00:45:22,172
After what happened with Lee Seong Jin,
you still don't get it?

640
00:45:23,005 --> 00:45:25,172
Threatening people, you punk,
assaulting them,

641
00:45:25,172 --> 00:45:27,497
and making them nod out of fear!

642
00:45:27,497 --> 00:45:29,305
Darn it!

643
00:45:29,305 --> 00:45:32,041
Forcing confessions to avoid beating!

644
00:45:32,041 --> 00:45:35,672
How much truth do you think there is
in a forced confession like that?

645
00:45:40,172 --> 00:45:43,338
Release Lee Ki Beom.

646
00:45:43,338 --> 00:45:47,505
Clean up your own mess
while I'm still giving you the chance.

647
00:45:47,505 --> 00:45:49,672
I can't do that.

648
00:45:54,538 --> 00:45:56,138
Fine!

649
00:45:56,938 --> 00:45:59,072
Then I'll do it my way.

650
00:46:00,305 --> 00:46:01,938
You just wait.

651
00:46:02,672 --> 00:46:05,225
I have

652
00:46:05,225 --> 00:46:07,805
learned a lot about you.

653
00:46:16,305 --> 00:46:18,805
Do whatever you want, you punk!

654
00:46:27,172 --> 00:46:29,038
You're late, huh?

655
00:46:30,872 --> 00:46:32,705
You are still up.

656
00:46:33,438 --> 00:46:35,838
Father went straight to Seoul for work.

657
00:46:35,838 --> 00:46:39,772
I'll be staying here for a while.

658
00:46:43,705 --> 00:46:46,038
Do I need to leave?

659
00:46:46,772 --> 00:46:50,238
I thought you felt uncomfortable
in this house.

660
00:46:53,605 --> 00:46:55,305
Good night.

661
00:47:25,472 --> 00:47:28,672
Fine! Then I'll do it my way.

662
00:47:28,672 --> 00:47:30,472
You just wait.

663
00:47:30,472 --> 00:47:32,105
I have

664
00:47:32,972 --> 00:47:35,605
learned a lot about you.

665
00:47:35,605 --> 00:47:37,772
How ridiculous.

666
00:47:38,438 --> 00:47:41,238
What could you possibly do?

667
00:47:45,955 --> 00:47:47,811
[Kangseng Police Station]

668
00:47:50,851 --> 00:47:53,496
Alright.

669
00:48:00,305 --> 00:48:01,638
Good night.

670
00:48:01,638 --> 00:48:05,205
My goodness, looks like
things got pretty intense.

671
00:48:06,072 --> 00:48:09,638
At least you didn't embarrass the police.

672
00:48:10,272 --> 00:48:11,872
Pardon?

673
00:48:14,211 --> 00:48:16,838
Darn it!

674
00:48:16,838 --> 00:48:19,438
So what do you want?

675
00:48:19,438 --> 00:48:22,805
Lee Ki Beom is not the real killer.

676
00:48:25,172 --> 00:48:29,372
He was illegally confined and beaten,
leading to a false confession.

677
00:48:35,605 --> 00:48:38,272
- Any evidence?
- There are signs

678
00:48:38,272 --> 00:48:40,105
of long-term assault on Lee Ki Beom's body.

679
00:48:40,105 --> 00:48:42,438
Come on, not that.

680
00:48:42,438 --> 00:48:45,472
If he's the real killer,
illegal detention and assault aren't issues.

681
00:48:45,472 --> 00:48:49,105
Do you have proof he's not the real killer?

682
00:48:49,105 --> 00:48:52,572
He has a solid alibi
for at least one of the murder dates.

683
00:48:52,572 --> 00:48:54,005
Because he was with me.

684
00:48:54,005 --> 00:48:55,772
Could that one case be a copycat crime?

685
00:48:55,772 --> 00:48:57,572
No.

686
00:48:57,572 --> 00:48:59,113
Because there clearly is a pattern
unique to the killer

687
00:48:59,113 --> 00:49:01,705
that hasn't been revealed to the public.

688
00:49:01,705 --> 00:49:03,338
Okay.

689
00:49:06,772 --> 00:49:09,172
Then your task is clear.

690
00:49:09,805 --> 00:49:12,905
I'll prove the injustices
Lee Ki Beom has suffered

691
00:49:14,005 --> 00:49:16,172
and catch the real killer.

692
00:49:17,638 --> 00:49:20,705
What do you need from me, then?

693
00:49:20,705 --> 00:49:23,538
Please allow Lee Ki Beom
to receive hospital treatment.

694
00:49:27,405 --> 00:49:29,072
Fine.

695
00:49:32,572 --> 00:49:36,572
[Pig Café]

696
00:49:48,005 --> 00:49:50,005
You don't seem like the type to work here.

697
00:49:50,005 --> 00:49:52,105
Not young, either.

698
00:49:52,105 --> 00:49:53,205
What?

699
00:49:53,205 --> 00:49:56,438
Didn't you come
because you heard we were hiring girls?

700
00:49:58,638 --> 00:50:00,777
[Ssanghwa Tea, Honey Tea, Coffee]
I'm not here for a job, but to find someone.

701
00:50:00,777 --> 00:50:03,972
[Seo Ji Won, Kangseng Daily]

702
00:50:03,972 --> 00:50:06,972
Someone? Who?

703
00:50:09,505 --> 00:50:11,838
Anyone who might recognize this purse.

704
00:50:13,872 --> 00:50:17,238
We usually require at least
one coffee order per girl here.

705
00:50:18,438 --> 00:50:19,505
You want one?

706
00:50:19,505 --> 00:50:22,305
Yes, please give me one.

707
00:50:23,405 --> 00:50:25,038
I don't know.

708
00:50:31,038 --> 00:50:33,772
- Two?
- Not coffee.

709
00:50:33,772 --> 00:50:35,772
Do you have ssanghwa tea?

710
00:50:36,905 --> 00:50:39,072
One ssanghwa tea here!

711
00:50:42,851 --> 00:50:46,038
So have you ever seen this purse?

712
00:50:49,738 --> 00:50:52,838
This is the one that man gave me.

713
00:51:16,838 --> 00:51:20,105
Go to the hospital and get treatment first.

714
00:51:21,205 --> 00:51:23,017
Thanks,

715
00:51:23,017 --> 00:51:24,372
Tae Joo.

716
00:51:28,438 --> 00:51:31,005
The killer is someone close to you.

717
00:51:31,005 --> 00:51:33,038
Friend or neighbor,
he's definitely in your circle.

718
00:51:33,038 --> 00:51:36,338
Blood type B, with hands
as delicate as a woman's.

719
00:51:37,472 --> 00:51:39,538
I don't know.

720
00:51:39,538 --> 00:51:41,872
No one comes to mind.

721
00:51:43,405 --> 00:51:46,938
Can't you even remember
where you lost your handkerchief?

722
00:51:48,338 --> 00:51:50,072
I'm sorry.

723
00:51:51,138 --> 00:51:54,305
It's nothing to apologize for,
so don't bow your head.

724
00:51:56,572 --> 00:51:58,205
I'm sorry

725
00:51:58,872 --> 00:52:01,038
for letting you go through
something like that.

726
00:52:03,072 --> 00:52:04,969
That's not

727
00:52:04,969 --> 00:52:07,372
something you should
be apologizing for, either.

728
00:52:08,505 --> 00:52:12,772
Then do you happen to know
where the bathhouse you were held at is?

729
00:52:12,772 --> 00:52:15,005
No. They covered my eyes.

730
00:52:15,005 --> 00:52:16,872
Those darn punks.

731
00:52:18,105 --> 00:52:21,805
We need someone who can testify
that you were illegally detained.

732
00:52:24,838 --> 00:52:26,438
There is.

733
00:52:28,338 --> 00:52:30,138
Someone who will testify.

734
00:52:50,272 --> 00:52:54,672
I was making a delivery, and he
suddenly jumped out. It was a mess.

735
00:52:54,672 --> 00:52:58,072
You can't just suddenly jump out like that!

736
00:53:01,138 --> 00:53:03,805
This is too much.

737
00:53:03,805 --> 00:53:06,505
It's not like you did it on purpose.

738
00:53:07,505 --> 00:53:09,838
I'm sorry about that day.

739
00:53:09,838 --> 00:53:14,272
He must've felt sorry,
so he came by and left it as a gift.

740
00:53:14,272 --> 00:53:15,905
But...

741
00:53:22,672 --> 00:53:26,038
[ID Card, Park Ae Sook]
There was a woman's ID inside.

742
00:53:26,838 --> 00:53:28,638
Do you think I'm some beggar?

743
00:53:28,638 --> 00:53:30,905
How could you give me some secondhand junk?

744
00:53:30,905 --> 00:53:32,705
Take it back!

745
00:53:34,338 --> 00:53:36,505
So I returned it.

746
00:53:36,505 --> 00:53:38,605
Who was that person?

747
00:53:39,305 --> 00:53:40,605
Some guy

748
00:53:40,605 --> 00:53:44,038
[Pig Café]
who works at the farm equipment repair shop.

749
00:53:45,072 --> 00:53:47,072
Im Seok Man.

750
00:53:47,072 --> 00:53:50,872
Seok Man saw me being taken away.

751
00:54:12,038 --> 00:54:15,005
Excuse me, are you Mr. Im Seok Man?

752
00:54:18,005 --> 00:54:21,105
I'm Reporter Seo Ji Won from Kangseng Daily.

753
00:54:21,105 --> 00:54:23,772
I have a few questions to ask you.

754
00:54:23,772 --> 00:54:26,838
Do you have a moment? It won't take long.

755
00:54:29,545 --> 00:54:31,529
Oh, dear.

756
00:54:35,572 --> 00:54:39,138
Oh, are you here for repair?

757
00:54:39,138 --> 00:54:42,538
Is there someone named Im Seok Man here?

758
00:54:42,538 --> 00:54:44,972
Try that store over there.

759
00:54:44,972 --> 00:54:46,172
Okay.

760
00:54:46,172 --> 00:54:51,172
Oh, Seok Man is quite popular.
A young lady came looking for him earlier.

761
00:54:51,172 --> 00:54:52,405
A young lady?

762
00:54:52,405 --> 00:54:55,505
Yeah, she was really pretty.

763
00:55:21,289 --> 00:55:26,307
[Seo Ji Won]

764
00:55:42,305 --> 00:55:44,425
Ouch!

765
00:55:44,425 --> 00:55:45,505
Ouch!

766
00:55:45,505 --> 00:55:46,772
Ji Won!

767
00:55:46,772 --> 00:55:48,772
Hey, Seo Ji Won!

768
00:55:48,772 --> 00:55:49,872
What are you doing, you little punk?

769
00:55:49,872 --> 00:55:52,072
Seo Ji Won, why are you here?
Are you hurt anywhere?

770
00:55:52,072 --> 00:55:54,438
No, it's nothing. It's nothing.

771
00:55:54,438 --> 00:55:58,305
I'm fine, I'm fine. Let go, quickly.

772
00:55:58,305 --> 00:56:01,738
Kang Tae Joo, why do you always
throw punches as soon as you see someone?

773
00:56:01,738 --> 00:56:03,072
- You...
- Hey!

774
00:56:03,072 --> 00:56:06,838
Seok Man was helping me remove the shards.

775
00:56:08,005 --> 00:56:10,938
Come on, there's one more here.

776
00:56:12,672 --> 00:56:14,372
Here, here.

777
00:56:14,372 --> 00:56:16,005
It's almost done.

778
00:56:22,472 --> 00:56:24,005
It's sharp. Please don't touch it.

779
00:56:24,005 --> 00:56:25,738
Oh, this...

780
00:56:27,605 --> 00:56:31,138
Ji Won, don't you recognize me?

781
00:56:31,138 --> 00:56:33,105
I'm Ki Beom's friend.

782
00:56:33,805 --> 00:56:35,272
You're Ki Beom's friend?

783
00:56:35,272 --> 00:56:38,705
You've paid for our drinks a few times.

784
00:56:38,705 --> 00:56:42,272
Oh? Oh yeah, right.

785
00:56:42,272 --> 00:56:44,438
Good to see you!

786
00:56:44,438 --> 00:56:46,038
Ji Won, blood...

787
00:56:51,072 --> 00:56:52,805
Thank you.

788
00:56:56,672 --> 00:57:01,272
So what brings you here, Reporter Seo?

789
00:57:01,272 --> 00:57:02,705
Well...

790
00:57:02,705 --> 00:57:05,605
Probably the same reason
as you, Detective Kang.

791
00:57:05,605 --> 00:57:07,372
- The purse!
- The witness?

792
00:57:08,238 --> 00:57:09,272
The purse?

793
00:57:09,272 --> 00:57:11,072
What witness?

794
00:57:16,105 --> 00:57:19,405
I found this purse.

795
00:57:19,405 --> 00:57:21,972
I didn't know there was an ID inside.

796
00:57:21,972 --> 00:57:23,438
I thought someone had thrown it away.

797
00:57:23,438 --> 00:57:26,638
Then you are the one
who left the purse in the bookstore?

798
00:57:27,605 --> 00:57:31,305
I thought if I left it there,
the owner would be able to find it.

799
00:57:31,305 --> 00:57:32,372
Why would you do that?

800
00:57:32,372 --> 00:57:35,772
You should have just put it back yourself.

801
00:57:37,305 --> 00:57:39,772
I was worried I'd be mistaken for a thief.

802
00:57:41,672 --> 00:57:42,705
This is driving me crazy.

803
00:57:42,705 --> 00:57:46,838
Wait, if this is all true, doesn't that mean
Ki Beom can clear his name?

804
00:57:46,838 --> 00:57:49,572
Right, if this guy just testifies.

805
00:57:49,572 --> 00:57:50,605
You'll testify, right?

806
00:57:50,605 --> 00:57:52,272
Of course I will. It's all because of me.

807
00:57:52,272 --> 00:57:53,538
Right, of course.

808
00:57:53,538 --> 00:57:54,638
Let's go, right away!

809
00:57:54,638 --> 00:57:56,672
Right... right now?

810
00:57:56,672 --> 00:57:58,438
Why? Is that a problem?

811
00:57:58,438 --> 00:58:00,838
Can I finish what I was working on first?

812
00:58:00,838 --> 00:58:02,605
The boss told me to finish it today.

813
00:58:02,605 --> 00:58:04,572
- How long will it take?
- 10 minutes, no...

814
00:58:04,572 --> 00:58:05,705
I can finish it in 5 minutes.

815
00:58:05,705 --> 00:58:07,338
Go ahead then.

816
00:58:07,338 --> 00:58:09,405
- I'll be right back.
- Alright.

817
00:58:14,238 --> 00:58:16,672
This is really good news.

818
00:58:16,672 --> 00:58:19,272
Ki Hwan and Sun Young
can finally breathe easier.

819
00:58:19,272 --> 00:58:21,105
You're right.

820
00:58:21,872 --> 00:58:23,605
Jeez, that kid.

821
00:58:23,605 --> 00:58:26,572
He witnessed Ki Beom

822
00:58:26,572 --> 00:58:28,238
being illegally detained...

823
00:58:39,205 --> 00:58:42,372
He was limping, like he was injured.

824
00:58:42,372 --> 00:58:44,105
I swear it's true!

825
00:58:50,872 --> 00:58:55,172
Hey, Tae Joo! Where are you going?

826
00:59:22,805 --> 00:59:24,738
High titanium levels would mean

827
00:59:24,738 --> 00:59:28,672
the person has been exposed
to a titanium-rich environment.

828
00:59:28,672 --> 00:59:34,205
He could be a worker in a factory
that handles alloys or welding.

829
00:59:34,205 --> 00:59:36,538
What about sodium and chlorine?

830
00:59:36,538 --> 00:59:40,405
Those are the main components of sweat.

831
00:59:40,405 --> 00:59:43,272
He's likely someone who sweats a lot.

832
00:59:43,272 --> 00:59:48,338
The killer could be a factory worker
who's constantly drenched in sweat,

833
00:59:48,338 --> 00:59:49,938
is that it?

834
00:59:49,938 --> 00:59:51,572
Probably.

835
00:59:56,272 --> 00:59:58,105
There you are.

836
01:00:01,472 --> 01:00:03,205
It's all done.

837
01:00:20,305 --> 01:00:22,838
As a police officer, it was my negligence.

838
01:00:24,405 --> 01:00:28,838
I should have realized sooner
that Ki Beom wasn't the real killer.

839
01:00:30,038 --> 01:00:32,038
Right.

840
01:00:32,038 --> 01:00:35,972
Only Ki Beom, who was innocent,
ended up suffering.

841
01:00:38,172 --> 01:00:39,838
Mr. Lee Yong Woo,

842
01:00:40,672 --> 01:00:43,738
don't you feel sorry for Ki Beom?

843
01:00:45,372 --> 01:00:47,138
Why would I?

844
01:00:48,705 --> 01:00:52,638
After all, Mr. Lee Yong Woo, he suffered

845
01:00:52,638 --> 01:00:54,838
because of your crimes, didn't he?

846
01:00:56,938 --> 01:00:59,338
It's not like I was the one
who put him in jail.

847
01:01:03,138 --> 01:01:04,905
You think so?

848
01:01:06,638 --> 01:01:11,872
Then is Ki Beom the friend you said you lost?

849
01:01:13,972 --> 01:01:16,638
I'll tell you that slowly.

850
01:01:19,172 --> 01:01:21,538
By the way, Professor,

851
01:01:22,538 --> 01:01:25,505
could you speak more casually?

852
01:01:25,505 --> 01:01:28,138
You were pretty casual with me back then.

853
01:01:30,038 --> 01:01:32,538
Is it because we haven't seen
each other in decades?

854
01:01:34,372 --> 01:01:36,705
You know me, right?

855
01:02:22,472 --> 01:02:23,472
Are you messing with me?

856
01:02:23,472 --> 01:02:24,972
What are you really up to?

857
01:02:24,972 --> 01:02:28,072
The special investigation team
has found another major suspect.

858
01:02:28,072 --> 01:02:29,805
The suspect is Im Seok Man, right?

859
01:02:29,805 --> 01:02:30,938
I need to check it out.

860
01:02:30,938 --> 01:02:32,572
Im Seok Man is type B.

861
01:02:32,572 --> 01:02:33,772
He's acquainted with Lee Ki Beom?

862
01:02:33,772 --> 01:02:37,272
If he's the real killer,
isn't that good for you too?

863
01:02:37,272 --> 01:02:39,905
I can't lose a friend like that again.

864
01:02:39,905 --> 01:02:42,905
So he was at the scene
of Lee Joo Hee's murder as well?

865
01:02:42,905 --> 01:02:45,838
Seok Man, what are you doing here
at this hour?

866
01:02:45,838 --> 01:02:48,238
I messed everything up.

867
01:02:48,238 --> 01:02:49,905
I...
